# Demo Builder (Fix Pass) — Maryland Driveway Restore

## Root cause identified and fixed

**The deploy-test FAIL was a single issue: WP admin login always returned to wp-login.php instead of landing on wp-admin.**

### Diagnosis

Direct WP-CLI confirmed `mdr_admin` and `demo_admin` users exist with correct roles. Direct login to the Docker container (`127.0.0.1:8081`) succeeded (302 + Set-Cookie auth cookies returned). Login via the public bridge failed.

Root cause: `urllib.request.urlopen` in the bridge follows HTTP redirects by default. When WP's POST /wp-login.php returns:
```
302 Found
Location: https://api.michaelwegter.com/demos/maryland-driveway-restore/wp-admin/
Set-Cookie: wordpress_logged_in_...  ← auth cookies
```
The bridge consumed the 302 itself (making an internal request to wp-admin), discarding the `Set-Cookie` headers. The browser never received the auth cookies, so every page visit after "login" was unauthenticated and WP immediately redirected back to wp-login.php.

### Fix

Added `_NoRedirect` handler to bridge blueprint — bridge now passes ALL 3xx responses through to the client unchanged, letting the browser handle the redirect and store auth cookies:

```python
class _NoRedirect(urllib.request.HTTPRedirectHandler):
    def redirect_request(self, req, fp, code, msg, hdrs, newurl):
        return None

_opener = urllib.request.build_opener(_NoRedirect())
# _opener.open(...) used instead of urllib.request.urlopen(...)
```

Committed `5210c3a`, pushed to mw-backend `main`. Auto-deploy restarted Flask within ~35s.

