## handoff
- produced: Bridge redirect bug fixed (commit 5210c3a); Playwright deploy-test now 20/20 PASS; WP admin login confirmed working end-to-end through the bridge.
- decisions: `_NoRedirect` handler is the correct architectural pattern for reverse-proxy bridges — any proxy that follows redirects will consume auth cookies from the 302 response; this fix applies globally (not login-specific).
- next needs: deploy-test step can now re-run and should PASS; then media-capture and proposal-writer can proceed.
- risks: `demo_admin` login still fails (likely stale password hash after container restart); `mdr_admin` is sufficient for the demo — proposal should advertise only `mdr_admin` credentials.
